text: Edward Adlebert Doisy (November 13, 1892 - October 23, 1986) was an American biochemist. He won the 1943 Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine, along with Henrik Dam, for the discovery of Vitamin K. ==References== Category:American biochemists Category:American Nobel Prize winners Category:Scientists from Illinois Category:1893 births Category:1986 deaths
